#Usage:
#------
video trim [files] [--start STARTTIME] [--duration DURATION]

#Description:
#------------
Cut a video to a part from STARTTIME to STARTTIME+DURATION of video files
using ffmpeg trimming function.
The times have to be in the format 00:00:00, whereby a starttime at minute 5
can also be defined with no leading zeros => 5:00

#Options:
#--------
--start STARTTIME     sets the time for the beginning of the trimmed version
		      => 5:32 begins at minute 5 and seconds 32

--duration DURATION   sets the duration of the cutted version
		      => 28 will cut a 28 seconds video

#Behavior:
#---------
- If no input files specified, video files in the current directory are listed for selection.
- Output files are named using the pattern: originalname_trimmed.ext
- Only common video file types are supported: .mp4, .mkv, .webm, .avi, .mov, .flv

#Examples:
#---------
video interpolate sample.mp4 --start 1:02:32 --duration 52:35
video interpolate video1.mkv --start 3:41 --duration 42

#Notes:
#------
- ffmpeg is not very precise when it comes to times.
  A few seconds of deviation can certainly occur.
